00:47:50,916 --> 00:47:52,076
I need her.

531
00:47:54,676 --> 00:47:57,037
So you will be accountable for her?

532
00:48:01,476 --> 00:48:02,516
Then it's done.

533
00:48:03,956 --> 00:48:05,796
-Her name is...
- I know who she is.

534
00:48:06,836 --> 00:48:08,116
Good day, Professor.

535
00:48:17,996 --> 00:48:20,916
Well, that went surprisingly well.

536
00:48:21,716 --> 00:48:23,316
You came off like a naive idiot.

537
00:48:24,956 --> 00:48:27,116
And naive idiots are not a threat.

538
00:48:42,476 --> 00:48:44,357
I'll come back when
the paperwork's complete.

539
00:48:52,396 --> 00:48:53,476
Are you all right?

540
00:48:53,556 --> 00:48:54,716
They didn't hurt me.

541
00:48:56,876 --> 00:48:59,196
They let a pregnant woman
into a room with a...

542
00:48:59,356 --> 00:49:01,236
It doesn't matter.

543
00:49:02,476 --> 00:49:04,156
They were stupid. I was stupid.

544
00:49:06,396 --> 00:49:07,677
Dyatlov won't talk to me.

545
00:49:09,396 --> 00:49:11,636
Akimov, yes, Toptunov, yes, but...

546
00:49:13,756 --> 00:49:14,876
Valery,

547
00:49:15,436 --> 00:49:16,516
AKimov...

548
00:49:17,876 --> 00:49:19,116
His face was gone.

549
00:49:22,356 --> 00:49:23,516
You want to stop?

550
00:49:25,716 --> 00:49:27,396
Is that a choice I even have?

551
00:49:35,876 --> 00:49:38,916
Do you think the fuel will actually
melt through the concrete pad?

552
00:49:38,996 --> 00:49:42,076
I don't know. A 40% chance, maybe.

553
00:49:45,156 --> 00:49:46,956
I said 50.

554
00:49:47,916 --> 00:49:49,956
Either way, the numbers
mean the same thing.

555
00:49:50,036 --> 00:49:51,076
"Maybe."

556
00:49:54,236 --> 00:49:56,636
Maybe the core will melt
through to the groundwater.

557
00:49:57,556 --> 00:49:59,716
Maybe the miners who I've told
to dig under the reactor

558
00:49:59,796 --> 00:50:01,396
will save millions of lives.

559
00:50:03,276 --> 00:50:04,836
Maybe I'm killing them for nothing.

560
00:50:08,916 --> 00:50:10,516
I don't want to do this anymore.

561
00:50:12,396 --> 00:50:13,516
I want to stop.

562
00:50:15,476 --> 00:50:16,516
But I can't.

563
00:50:18,276 --> 00:50:20,636
I don't think you have
a choice any more than I do.

564
00:50:22,556 --> 00:50:25,236
I think, despite the stupidity,

565
00:50:25,836 --> 00:50:27,596
the lies, even this,

566
00:50:28,516 --> 00:50:29,756
you are compelled.

567
00:50:30,716 --> 00:50:32,996
The problem has been assigned,
and you will stop at nothing

568
00:50:33,076 --> 00:50:34,316
until you find an answer.

569
00:50:34,396 --> 00:50:36,916
Because that is who you are.

570
00:50:39,076 --> 00:50:40,316
A lunatic, then.

571
00:50:42,796 --> 00:50:43,756
A scientist.

572
00:51:05,116 --> 00:51:07,276
Did you know that they were
running a safety test?

573
00:51:09,076 --> 00:51:10,036
Yeah.

574
00:51:10,116 --> 00:51:11,196
There's something else.

575
00:51:12,996 --> 00:51:16,036
Akimov says
they shut the reactor down,

576
00:51:16,116 --> 00:51:17,956
and Toptunov confirms it.

577
00:51:18,596 --> 00:51:19,716
They pressed AZ-5.

578
00:51:19,996 --> 00:51:21,636
Apparently not soon enough.

579
00:51:22,116 --> 00:51:23,156
No.

580
00:51:23,756 --> 00:51:27,396
They say Akimov pressed AZ-5,

581
00:51:28,236 --> 00:51:30,116
and then the reactor exploded.

582
00:51:32,356 --> 00:51:34,996
If it had been just one of them,
I would have put it under

583
00:51:35,076 --> 00:51:37,836
faulty memory or delusion even,

584
00:51:37,916 --> 00:51:40,516
but they both agreed.
They were adamant.

585
00:51:44,956 --> 00:51:45,996
Comrade?

586
00:51:48,916 --> 00:51:49,956
Do you think it's possible?

587
00:51:50,036 --> 00:51:51,556
I think it makes no sense. I...

588
00:51:52,276 --> 00:51:55,356
I think it's what I would say if
I was trying to cover my own mistakes.

589
00:51:55,955 --> 00:51:56,915
But?

590
00:51:58,116 --> 00:51:59,236
I believe them.

591
00:52:01,956 --> 00:52:03,316
Then you should pursue it.

592
00:52:03,915 --> 00:52:06,436
We have to pursue every possibility,

593
00:52:07,276 --> 00:52:09,036
no matter how unlikely,

594
00:52:09,836 --> 00:52:12,076
no matter what or who's to blame.

595
00:52:14,276 --> 00:52:17,396
I'll go back to the hospital
and re-interview Akimov and Toptunov.

596
00:52:20,756 --> 00:52:21,796
If they're still awake.

597
00:52:23,516 --> 00:52:24,516
They're not.

598
00:52:26,756 --> 00:52:27,716
Khomyuk.

